&lt;h3 id=&#34;K-diff-pairs-in-an-Array&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#K-diff-pairs-in-an-Array&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;K-diff pairs in an Array&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/k-diff-pairs-in-an-array/&#34;&gt;K-diff pairs in an Array&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a name=&#34;k-diff-pairs-in-an-array&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pretty intuitive solution. Build a frequency HashMap for all the numbers in the array. In a special case where &lt;code&gt;diff&lt;/code&gt; is 0, just count occurences in our &lt;code&gt;freq&lt;/code&gt; map whose values are 2 or more. In other case, just loop through all the keys and make sure it’s supplement exists to count the number of K-diff pairs.&lt;/p&gt;
