&lt;h3 id=&#34;Binary-Search-Tree-Iterator&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Binary-Search-Tree-Iterator&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Binary Search Tree Iterator&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/binary-search-tree-iterator/&#34;&gt;Binary Search Tree Iterator&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a name=&#34;binary-search-tree-iterator&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Runtime: 15 ms, faster than 99.74% of Java online submissions for Binary Search Tree Iterator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Memory Usage: 49.9 MB, less than 93.83% of Java online submissions for Binary Search Tree Iterator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Logic is same as your In-Order traversal of any Binary Tree, but store the node values you visit in any data structure. Here I am using an ArrayList for storing each of the visited node’s value. Maintain &lt;code&gt;idx&lt;/code&gt; value to keep track of which value to return. &lt;code&gt;hasNext()&lt;/code&gt; method returns true as long as &lt;code&gt;idx &amp;lt; list.size()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
